Verant did this on <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>purpose</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> to stop people from dieing when zoneing on low health.  <br>
I believe it had to deal with the way your character talked to the server when zoneing.  Before they did this change, people were dieing after zoneing, even though they had more than enough hp when they did zone.<br>
Will try to find the specific patch message if there was one.  Just know that for now, if they hadn't changed it to strip your buffs, you'd be dead every time, instead of zoneing and losing all your buffs, and living.<br>
<br>
-EDIT-<br>
I found the link.<br>
Here is the Q/A from the this eq castersrealm <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://eq.castersrealm.com/viewarticle.asp?Article=3322">Article</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> 7. Losing all your buffs because you had fewer hitpoints than given to you via hitpoint gear. The system thinks you didn't have any hitpoints. (Change the system to check for hitpoint gear before checking for how many hitpoints you have, and THEN calculate whether you zoned while dying.) <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> From what I hear about this one, if we fix it you're more likely to come out on the other side dead. Essentially the bug is preventing death while zoning, fixing it would be a nerf, actually. Or at least that's how I understand it…<br>
-Alan</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
